Text.SourceString: Every grain of sand holds a universe of possibilities. It's not just sand; it's the potential for beauty.
Text.LocalizedString: Every grain of sand holds a universe of possibilities. It's not just sand; it's the potential for beauty.

Text.SourceString: I earn a decent amount of money from my sculptures. It's not a fortune, but it's enough...
Text.LocalizedString: I earn a decent amount of money from my sculptures. It's not a fortune, but it's enough...

Text.SourceString: I once spent a full moon talking to a starfish, learning its patterns for my art. Fascinating conversation.
Text.LocalizedString: I once spent a full moon talking to a starfish, learning its patterns for my art. Fascinating conversation.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes I lose track of time and forget to sleep. Down here where it doesn't really get dark, it's hard to tell when to rest.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes I lose track of time and forget to sleep. Down here where it doesn't really get dark, it's hard to tell when to rest.

Text.SourceString: Ah, hello there. I'm <NPCName>Galoong</>. I, um, I work with sculptures...//It's nice to meet you.
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, hello there. I'm <NPCName>Galoong</>. I, um, I work with sculptures...//It's nice to meet you.

Text.SourceString: Ah, <NPCName>Rysy</>. She may not be the chattiest fish in the sea, but give her a needle, and she creates magic.
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, <NPCName>Rysy</>. She may not be the chattiest fish in the sea, but give her a needle, and she creates magic.

Text.SourceString: Have you seen <NPCName>Rysy</>'s latest piece? Wow!
Text.LocalizedString: Have you seen <NPCName>Rysy</>'s latest piece? Wow!

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Rysy</>'s a bit of a mystery. Doesn't mingle much.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Rysy</>'s a bit of a mystery. Doesn't mingle much.

Text.SourceString: I might seem a bit out of the current, but isn't that what art is about? Swimming against the tide.
Text.LocalizedString: I might seem a bit out of the current, but isn't that what art is about? Swimming against the tide.

Text.SourceString: Days? I thought it was still morning. Time flows differently down here.
Text.LocalizedString: Days? I thought it was still morning. Time flows differently down here.

Text.SourceString: This sculpture here is a tribute to the coral reefs, a reminder of what we must protect.
Text.LocalizedString: This sculpture here is a tribute to the coral reefs, a reminder of what we must protect.

Text.SourceString: I refuse to use anything that harms our waters. My art is a celebration of the sea, not its destruction.
Text.LocalizedString: I refuse to use anything that harms our waters. My art is a celebration of the sea, not its destruction.

Text.SourceString: This piece here tells the story of a dolphin ensnared in nets. Heartbreaking.
Text.LocalizedString: This piece here tells the story of a dolphin ensnared in nets. Heartbreaking.

Text.SourceString: We must create as nature does – with care, with respect, with an eye for the future.
Text.LocalizedString: We must create as nature does – with care, with respect, with an eye for the future.

Text.SourceString: This coral, glowing under the moon, took me three tides to find. But look how it catches the light.
Text.LocalizedString: This coral, glowing under the moon, took me three tides to find. But look how it catches the light.

Text.SourceString: When farming, be gentle with your tools. Treat them as an extension of your own fins.
Text.LocalizedString: When farming, be gentle with your tools. Treat them as an extension of your own fins.

Text.SourceString: Don't rush your craft. The tides don't hurry, yet they shape entire coastlines.
Text.LocalizedString: Don't rush your craft. The tides don't hurry, yet they shape entire coastlines.

Text.SourceString: I once lived among the surface folk. Their world, their art, it's different, yet the same.
Text.LocalizedString: I once lived among the surface folk. Their world, their art, it's different, yet the same.

Text.SourceString: There are chapters of my life closed like an oyster's shell. Not all stories need to be told.
Text.LocalizedString: There are chapters of my life closed like an oyster's shell. Not all stories need to be told.

Text.SourceString: The sea keeps many secrets, and so do I. Perhaps that's why we understand each other.
Text.LocalizedString: The sea keeps many secrets, and so do I. Perhaps that's why we understand each other.

Text.SourceString: I once had a heart tied to the land above. Different world, different...challenges.
Text.LocalizedString: I once had a heart tied to the land above. Different world, different...challenges.

Text.SourceString: Ah, the surface. I've had my share of memories there. Not all of them as bright as the sun that shines above it.
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, the surface. I've had my share of memories there. Not all of them as bright as the sun that shines above it.

Text.SourceString: There was someone, up there on land. It didn't...well, let's just say the tides turned, and so did my heart.
Text.LocalizedString: There was someone, up there on land. It didn't...well, let's just say the tides turned, and so did my heart.

Text.SourceString: I've learned much since then. The surface has its allure, but it's not where my soul swims at peace.
Text.LocalizedString: I've learned much since then. The surface has its allure, but it's not where my soul swims at peace.

Text.SourceString: I find joy here, among the waves and reefs. The depth of the sea is more my home than any land above.
Text.LocalizedString: I find joy here, among the waves and reefs. The depth of the sea is more my home than any land above.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Vihren</> and I found this hidden cove last tide, the one near the surface with all the lights. It's so very pretty.//<portrait=normal>It's become our little sanctuary.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Vihren</> and I found this hidden cove last tide, the one near the surface with all the lights. It's so very pretty.//<portrait=normal>It's become our little sanctuary.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Vihren</>'s more than just my partner. He's my anchor in stormy waters, my calm during high tides.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Vihren</>'s more than just my partner. He's my anchor in stormy waters, my calm during high tides.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Vihren</>'s been teaching me about the constellations. We lie on the ocean's surface, stargazing.//It's our shared passion.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Vihren</>'s been teaching me about the constellations. We lie on the ocean's surface, stargazing.//It's our shared passion.

Text.SourceString: I tried making that seaweed stew for dinner last night. <NPCName>Vihren</> ate it, but I could tell he's not a fan of kelp noodles.//It took him a good minute to chew every time.
Text.LocalizedString: I tried making that seaweed stew for dinner last night. <NPCName>Vihren</> ate it, but I could tell he's not a fan of kelp noodles.//It took him a good minute to chew every time.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Vihren</> and I were organizing our art supplies yesterday. He's so particular about keeping his brushes separate. I just lump mine together!
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Vihren</> and I were organizing our art supplies yesterday. He's so particular about keeping his brushes separate. I just lump mine together!

Text.SourceString: Last tide, I surprised <NPCName>Vihren</> with a moonlight swim. Turns out, he's not too keen on cold currents. We ended up watching the plankton glow from a warmer spot.
Text.LocalizedString: Last tide, I surprised <NPCName>Vihren</> with a moonlight swim. Turns out, he's not too keen on cold currents. We ended up watching the plankton glow from a warmer spot.

Text.SourceString: I made one of those surface desserts for <NPCName>Vihren</> – you know, the sweet ones? He loved it, but said it was a bit too sugary for him.//<portrait=normal>Maybe less sea sugar next time.
Text.LocalizedString: I made one of those surface desserts for <NPCName>Vihren</> – you know, the sweet ones? He loved it, but said it was a bit too sugary for him.//<portrait=normal>Maybe less sea sugar next time.

Text.SourceString: Many moons ago, I used to spend my days up in the far north, teaching young merlings how to shape stones into small figurines. They were quick learners, those little ones.//Oh, but not around here – it's in the far north.
Text.LocalizedString: Many moons ago, I used to spend my days up in the far north, teaching young merlings how to shape stones into small figurines. They were quick learners, those little ones.//Oh, but not around here – it's in the far north.

Text.SourceString: Every so often, I swim into the kelp forest with <NPCName>Etna</> to forage for some sea grapes. They taste different, the ones growing there.
Text.LocalizedString: Every so often, I swim into the kelp forest with <NPCName>Etna</> to forage for some sea grapes. They taste different, the ones growing there.

Text.SourceString: I tried my fins at seaweed baking. It's trickier than it looks, but the crispy result is worth it.
Text.LocalizedString: I tried my fins at seaweed baking. It's trickier than it looks, but the crispy result is worth it.

Text.SourceString: I've been experimenting with different types of sea berries in our recipes. They add such a unique flavor.//<portrait=happy><NPCName>Olan</> got a bunch for us to share.
Text.LocalizedString: I've been experimenting with different types of sea berries in our recipes. They add such a unique flavor.//<portrait=happy><NPCName>Olan</> got a bunch for us to share.

Text.SourceString: Cooking with what you forage yourself just feels different, more rewarding.
Text.LocalizedString: Cooking with what you forage yourself just feels different, more rewarding.

Text.SourceString: I made a kelp and sea cucumber salad. Simple, but delicious. It's amazing what you can do with fresh ingredients.
Text.LocalizedString: I made a kelp and sea cucumber salad. Simple, but delicious. It's amazing what you can do with fresh ingredients.

Text.SourceString: I had an interesting conversation with <NPCName>Jannu</>, the sous-chef. He's got some wild ideas about fusion cooking, like sea grapes and coconut leaves.//<portrait=concerned>Oh no, you heard right – not the fruit, the leaves.
Text.LocalizedString: I had an interesting conversation with <NPCName>Jannu</>, the sous-chef. He's got some wild ideas about fusion cooking, like sea grapes and coconut leaves.//<portrait=concerned>Oh no, you heard right – not the fruit, the leaves.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Agung</> showed me some pearls that might inspire my next piece. Their luster is unlike any I've seen.//<portrait=normal>He found them near the gate. I told him to put them back, though – a clam might be looking for them.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Agung</> showed me some pearls that might inspire my next piece. Their luster is unlike any I've seen.//<portrait=normal>He found them near the gate. I told him to put them back, though – a clam might be looking for them.

Text.SourceString: Noticed a group of young dolphins learning to ride the currents. Reminds me of my early swimming days.
Text.LocalizedString: Noticed a group of young dolphins learning to ride the currents. Reminds me of my early swimming days.

Text.SourceString: The bioluminescent plankton in the deep sea have been extra bright these nights. It's like swimming through a sea of stars.
Text.LocalizedString: The bioluminescent plankton in the deep sea have been extra bright these nights. It's like swimming through a sea of stars.

Text.SourceString: The seawater's been warmer lately. It changes the way the light plays through the water. Quite beautiful.
Text.LocalizedString: The seawater's been warmer lately. It changes the way the light plays through the water. Quite beautiful.

Text.SourceString: There's a new school of fish that's migrated into our area. They're so colorful and lively.
Text.LocalizedString: There's a new school of fish that's migrated into our area. They're so colorful and lively.

Text.SourceString: The tides have been gentle this week. Makes for a peaceful swim, especially in the mornings.
Text.LocalizedString: The tides have been gentle this week. Makes for a peaceful swim, especially in the mornings.
